*Says No Cause For Alarm Over APC Muslim-Muslim Ticket ABUJA – The Chairman, Senate Committee on Information and National Orientation, Senator Danladi Sankara on Wednesday, described the candidacy of All Progressives Congress (APC) Presidential hopefuls, Bola Tinubu and Senator Kashim Shettima as “competent, cerebral and tested.” He also commended Tinubu’s choice of the former Borno State governor as one that has “brightened the chances of the All Progressives Congress (APC) to secure victory in the general election scheduled for next year, 2023.” A statement by Muhammad Nazifi, Media Aide to Senator Sankara, revealed that the Lawmaker made the remark while addressing party leaders and supporters during the week in Jigawa State. The Jigawa North West Senator also expressed confidence in the wisdom of the APC presidential candidate, saying that the team will add value to the presidency. He explained that “by the choice of Senator Kashim Shettima as his running mate for the next year general election Asiwaju Bola Tinubu has proved himself as a leader with great wisdom and vision to assemble capable people to assist him to provide the desired leadership that would improve the welfare of Nigerians. “We are together with him in this 9th Senate and everyone is aware of his leadership capabilities, he will complement the efforts of Asiwaju Bola Tinubu to bring about the desired progress and development of the nation.” Senator Sankara further pointed out that there was no cause for alarm or apprehension by any group over the party’s Muslim-Muslim ticket, adding that both men are very conscious of the requirements of equity and justice in leadership and public administration.